<br>
What it also means is you accept the fact that a woman may choose to actually excercise that right, and have an abortion.  <br>
<br>
How, then, is this not considered being Pro-Abortion?  It's hiding behind a thin veil of words.  If it's not ok with you that a person makes a certain choice, then you're not actually Pro-Choice.  Having a choice means the possibility of making more than one decision, otherwise it's not a choice.  If you don't accept that one of those decisions is to abort, you can not be Pro-Choice.  So why maintain this farce of names?  You're either Anti-Abortion or Pro-Abortion.  It could also be acceptable to have no opinion.  But Pro-Choice?  A completely fabricated term that doesn't describe the situation at all.  <p>-Tain<BR>
